<H3> <TI>   Sony, Texas Instruments Agree on Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0803091894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0804 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0803091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 8 KYODO -- Sony Corp. said Tuesday [8 
March] it has agreed to license its 16-bit microcontroller unit 
(MCU) technology to Texas Instruments Japan Ltd. 
  Under the agreement, the Japanese subsidiary of the U.S. 
semiconductor manufacturer will develop, produce and market MCUs 
using Sony technology, Sony said. 
  The MCU forms the brain of a wide range of electronics 
products, including videocassette recorders and personal 
computers. 
  The companies will also study the possibility of joint 
16-bit 
MCU development and technology sharing in the area of MCU 
peripheral circuitry, Sony said. 
  In addition, the companies will discuss the incorporation of 
MCUs developed by Texas Instruments Japan in Sony's audiovisual 
products, Sony said. 

</TEXT>

