<H3> <TI>   FTC Searches Contractors for Bid Rigging Proof </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0803091694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0801 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0803091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 8 KYODO -- The Fair Trade Commission 
(FTC) searched the offices of a contractors' association and 
over 20 member companies in Tochigi Prefecture on Tuesday [8 
March] for evidence of suspected bid rigging, commission 
officials said. 
  The companies are suspected of illegally conspiring to 
repeatedly fix bidding prices for municipal and prefectural 
public works projects. 
  The prefectural association's branch office in Utsunomiya, 
north of Tokyo, which lists 146 engineering works companies, was 
subjected to the compulsory search. 
  The searches were the first by the FTC since it investigated 
a contractors' association in Yamanashi Prefecture last May. 

</TEXT>

