<H3> <TI>   Takemura Pledges `Support' to Hosokawa 2 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303130794 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 3 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0303130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In response to Prime Minister Hosokawa's decision 
to put off a cabinet reshuffle, Chief Cabinet Secretary Takemura 
met with the prime minister at the latter's official residence 
on the evening of 2 March. During the meeting, the chief cabinet 
secretary told the prime minister: "I am sorry for causing 
various troubles. I would like to solicit your continued 
favors." In this way, the chief cabinet secretary expressed to 
the prime minister his intention to support the latter as chief 
cabinet secretary. The prime minister responded, "You and I work 
in the same office and your apology sounds awkward." 

</TEXT>

