<H3> <TI>   `Outcome' of Ochirbat's Visit to Laos Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0303213494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 2028 GMT 3 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0303213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 3 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian President P. Ochirbat's official visit to the LPDR 
[Lao People's Democratic Republic] ended as it was noted by the 
president of Mongolia P. Ochirbat and the president of the LPDR 
Nouhak Phoumsavan, the both sides are fully satisfied with the 
outcome of the bilateral meeting and negotiations. 
  Before leaving the country, the presidents signed the treaty 
on friendly relations and cooperation between Mongolia and the 
LPDR. Signed were also the agreement on encouragement and 
protection of investments and the plan of cooperation between 
the Ministries of Health of the two countries for 1994-1996 by 
the heads of the corresponding departments. 
  Within the framework of the visit of the Mongolian president 
the meetings of parliamentarians of the two countries were held. 

</TEXT>

