<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decrease in Secondary School Students Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0203192294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1730 GMT 2 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0203192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- At the 
secondary schools of Mongolia there are studying some 370 
thousand children. This is approximately by ten thousand less 
than during the last year. More than 92 thousand schoolchildren 
have stopped attending their lessons for the current schooling 
year. Such a weakening children's interest in study is being 
promoted by a number of objective and subjective factors. Among 
them one can see such as a formalistic attitude to the teaching 
in schools, low level professional skill of some teachers and at 
last financial difficulties arising in the transition period to 
a market. Last winter some 86 schools had to cease their 
studies due to the absence of heating supply to their 
schoolbuildings. For many of schools in the countryside there 
is a serious lack of teaching staff. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

