<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice Foreign Minister Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0903114494 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 1100 GMT 9 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0903114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After attending a training course for the district 
chapter chairmen of the Democratic Liberal Party, Vice Foreign 
Minister Hong Sun-yong said today that the inspection of North 
Korea by the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] had not 
reached a point that would be acceptable to us, and that the 
North-South dialogue had not proceeded smoothly. It is therefore 
not clear whether the third round of U.S.-North Korean 
high-level talks will be held on 21 March as scheduled. 
  Vice Foreign Minister Hong said: If the talks are not held 
as scheduled, the North Korean nuclear issue cannot but return 
to the starting point. Considering this, the government has 
continued to discuss the presentation of the nuclear issue to 
the UN Security Council with friendly countries, such as the 
United States. 

</TEXT>

