<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Visit by Romanian President Iliescu </TI></H3>
<H4>   Romanian President Arrives 9 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> SK0903053594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0149 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0903053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 9 (YONHAP) -- Romanian President Ion 
Iliescu arrived in Seoul Wednesday for a three-day visit 
emphasizing economic cooperation with South Korea. Iliescu, 
Romania's first popularly elected president, meets with his 
South Korean counterpart Kim Yong-sam later in the afternoon and 
will be the main guest at a state dinner. He will meet leaders 
from both the ruling and opposition camps on Thursday. But the 
highlight of his visit is an industrial tour and meetings with 
business leaders that will take him to the southern part of the 
country for a first-hand look at factories, with 22 businessmen 
accompanying him. 
  Romania had been a staunch ally of North Korea until 
Iliescu's election as president, and Seoul officials see his 
visit as another sign of the cold war's collapse. 
  Kim and Iliescu will issue a joint statement after their 
summit pledging to pursue dialogue on political and economic 
cooperation. The two countries' foreign ministers will sign an 
aviation agreement on Thursday. 

</TEXT>

