<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Loan Approved for Romania's Telecommunications </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0903014694 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD in English 9 Mar 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> SK0903014694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Export-Import [Ex-Im] Bank of Korea has agreed 
with Romania's state-run telecommunications corporation to 
extend a $50 million loan from the Economic Development 
Cooperation Fund (EDCF), a spokesman said. 
  The agreement was signed in Bucharest last Friday (local 
time) between Ex-Im Bank president Kim Yong-pin and Dumitru 
Anghelescu, president of the communications corporation Rom 
Telecom R.A. 
  The EDCF loan carries an annual interest of 4.2 percent and 
has to be paid back over the next 20 years with five years' 
deferment of repayments of the principal. 
  The state-run telecommunications company will use the loan 
for modernizing communications equipment in the Romanian state 
of Prahova. 
  Signed prior to the state visit of Romanian President Ion 
Iliescu today, the agreement is expected to boost bilateral 
economic cooperation and to help Korean companies export 
machinery and equipment to East European countries, the 
spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

