<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alatas Opposes U.S. Blockade Against Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903130594 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0903130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Indonesian Government cannot accept the U.S. 
blockade against Cuba because every country has the right to 
adopt its own political and economic system without the 
interference of other countries. Speaking to reporters after he 
met with Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina in Jakarta 
today, Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said Indonesia has firmly 
adopted such a stand as the basis of its international 
relations, adding that Indonesia also believes that a country 
should not impose its will on another country, especially by 
imposing a blockade. 
  Speaking to reporters, Cuban Foreign Minister Robaina said 
his visit to Indonesia is part of his tour of seven Asian 
countries in his country's efforts to oppose the economic 
blockade imposed by the United States for the last 30 years. 

</TEXT>

