<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Clears Southern Luzon of NPA Rebels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903063294 Manila MANILA BULLETIN in English 5 Mar 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> BK0903063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Manila MANILA BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Rolly Alano] </F>
  [Text] Camp Martillana, Pili Camarines Sur -- The 
Philippine Army has cleared all barangays [villages] affected by 
the New People's Army (NPA) in the Bicol region, Quezon, and 
other parts of southern Luzon, Brig. Gen. Regino Lacson, 
Southern Luzon Command (Solcom) chief reported yesterday. 
  Lacson said that six guerrilla fronts of the NPA controlled 
533 barangays in the three zones last year, adding that these 
controlled barangays were key "promotion" areas for the NPAs. 
From these barangays, rebels took "taxation money," rice, 
livestock, and vegetable crops for their maintenance, Lacson 
said. They were the single, most important source of income for 
the rebel movement in the three zones, he added. 

</TEXT>

