<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   PULO Claims Responsibility for Railroad Mine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0803161994 Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 in Thai 
1200 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0803161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] A locomotive was damaged when it hit a mine 
planted on a bridge between the Hat Yai and Chana rail stations. 
The locomotive was on its way to pull a train with a load of 
rock from Chana back to Hat Yai. The incident took place at 0506 
today in Ban Thung Phra, Tambon Paching, Chana District, 
Songkhla Province, only three kilometers from the Chana station. 
The explosion damaged the front of the locomotive and the 
tracks. The driver and engineer were unhurt. 
  Authorities found two letters from the PULO [Pattani United 
Liberation Organization], one written in southern dialect and 
the other in Thai, claiming responsibility for the incident. 
They want the government explain the motive behind the recent 
torching of schools in the south which, they said, was not the 
work of the PULO. 

</TEXT>

