<H3> <TI>   Keating: Super 301 `Heavy-Handed Sledgehammer' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903073294 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 9 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0903073294 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Paul Keating, has accused the 
United States of using a sledgehammer to crack a nut in its 
trade dispute with Japan. The United States has reintroduced 
its so-called Super 301 policy where it can double tariffs on 
some commodities in a bid to get Japan to open its markets. 
Speaking in Perth, Mr. Keating urged the two parties to allow 
the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation forum, APEC, to resolve 
the dispute. The prime minister says Canberra is concerned that 
America's action will harm Australia's relationship with Japan. 
  [Begin Keating recording] It is the heavy-handed 
sledgehammer 
number to crack the nut. Now, we think that is going to lead to 
a lot of bilateral trade tensions and that is why, I think, that 
we see the body which I was involved in last year in 
establishing at the head of government level -- this is the 
APEC, Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation -- this trade argument 
between the United States and Japan is a sitter for resolution 
within the APEC framework. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

