<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lao Defense Minister, Delegation Conclude Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0803162094 Hanoi VNA in English 1437 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0803162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 8.-- A high-level military 
delegation of Laos, led by Defence Minister Sr. Lt. Gen. 
Choummali Sai-gnason, left here this afternoon, winding up a 
4-day official visit to Vietnam. 
  While here, the Lao delegation held talks with a high level 
military delegation of Vietnam led by Defense Minister Gen. Doan 
Khue. The two sides informed each other of the situation in 
their respective countries. They noted with satisfaction that 
despite sweeping changes in the world and the region in recent 
years, the relationship between the two countries and armies 
kept on developing, thereby making active contributions to 
building their countries, and to peace, cooperation and 
stability in the region. 
  Both sides compared notes on the building of the army, the 
all-people national defence and on issues of common concern. 
The two sides reaffirmed their determination to foster the 
special friendship and solidarity between the peoples and armies 
of Vietnam and Laos. A protocol on the friendly cooperation 
between Lao and Vietnamese armies was signed today by Sr. Lt. 
Gen. Siphon Phalikhan, vice defence minister of Laos, and Lt. 
Gen. Nguyen Thoi Bung, vice defence minister of Vietnam. 
Vietnamese and Lao defence Ministers Doan Khue and Choummali 
Sai-gnason witnessed the signing. Earlier, the Lao delegation 
paid a floral tribute to late President Ho Chi Minh at his 
mausoleum. It was received by Party General Secretary Do Muoi. 

</TEXT>

