<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Denounces Japan's `Nuclear Armament Maneuvers' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0903085994 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1153 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0903085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1153 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Yun Pyong-son: "Japan's Nuclear Armament </F>
Maneuvers Have Reached a Dangerous Stage"] 
  [Text] According to reports, Japan's Monju, a fast breeder 
reactor built in Tsuruga city, Fukui Prefecture, will soon begin 
operating as the transportation of plutonium fuel needed has 
been completed. This is one of Japan's undisguised attempts to 
secure large quantities of plutonium for itself so as to produce 
nuclear weapons at any time and become a nuclear power. 
  Japan's nuclear armament maneuvers are accelerating to a 
very 
dangerous stage. According to data, Japan, which has stockpiled 
26 tonnes of plutonium, will increase its reserve to 100 tonnes 
by 2010. This is a huge amount, enough for over 10,000 nuclear 
bombs. 
  Japan has developed not only elements and technology for the 
production of a nuclear bomb, including the electronic 
destructive device, but also devices for long-range nuclear 
transportation. This has been proven by the fact that Japan 
developed the large long-range H-2 rocket, which can be used as 
an inter-continental ballistic missile in February 1994. 
  The world believes that it is only a matter of time until 
Japan will produce nuclear weapons. A Western paper reported 
that Japan may have already produced them. In fact, Japan could 
become a nuclear power in a very short time whenever it is 
determined to do so. These facts clearly show to what a 
dangerous stage Japan's nuclear armament has come. 
  What cannot be overlooked is that Japanese authorities and 
politicians, who are promoting full-scale nuclear armament, are 
playing mean making an issue out of the so-called nuclear issue 
of ours. Former Japanese Prime Minister Nakasone recently raved 
that the UN Security Council should keep the possibility of 
imposing economic sanctions open in case we refuse special 
inspections. Japanese Foreign Minister Hata said the pressure 
for inspection on our military facilities will increase and 
urged that measures be taken to dispel suspicion over nuclear 
weapons development. 
  As everyone knows, there is no mention of "special 
inspection" in the recently announced agreement reached at the 
DPRK-U.S. contact in New York. In any regard, Japan is not in a 
position to intervene in the resolution of the nuclear issue on 
the Korean peninsula. The reason the Japanese reactionaries 
have recently started playing mean by becoming more feverish in 
the special inspection commotion is to impede the settlement of 
the nuclear issue and find a pretext for the lawful promotion of 
the nuclear armament, which has reached the danger line. 
  It is the most vicious and shameless intention of the 
Japanese reactionaries that they are picking on others while it 
is themselves who are accelerating the nuclear armament. It is 
not difficult to estimate how enormous the effect on the peace 
of Asia and the world might be when the Monju fast breeder 
reactor begins operating and large quantities of plutonium are 
secured for the manufacture of nuclear weapons. 
  Some Japanese reactionaries even insist on becoming a 
military power and dispatching more of the Self-Defense Forces 
overseas saying that Japan lost World War II because it was 
weak. It is obvious that our country may become a nuclear 
victim when the neighboring Japan, which is making every attempt 
to realize its old dream of the Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity 
Sphere, is even armed with nuclear weapons. 
  The denuclearization of Northeast Asia cannot be realized 
when Japan is arming itself with nuclear weapons. The 
North-South joint declaration on denuclearization will be 
invalid, and the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula will 
be virtually meaningless. 
  It is not a coincidence that the people of Asia and around 
the world, including our people, are showing grave concern over 
Japan's nuclear armament. It is a common desire of humanity to 
live in a peaceful world free of nuclear threat. People across 
the world should block and destroy Japan's maneuver to smoke 
nuclear clouds, running counter to mankind's wish. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must correctly realize the dear 
price they must pay for their maneuvers for nuclear armament and 
nuclear power and immediately abandon their criminal nuclear 
ambition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

