<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zimbabwe Friendship Association Holds Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0803214294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1514 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0803214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 8 (KCNA) -- An annual general 
meeting of the Zimbabwe-Korea Solidarity and Friendship 
Association was held in Harare, Zimbabwe on February 24. 
  Chairman of the association N.T. Mawema stressed in his 
report that the Korean people achieved great success in 
socialist construction, pushed aside the anti-DPRK and the 
anti-socialist moves of the imperialists and renegades of 
socialism and firmly defended the sovereignty of the DPRK under 
the tested guidance of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il last 
year. He called for conducting the active solidarity movement 
for defence of socialist Korea. 
  The general meeting discussed the question of significantly 
celebrating the 82nd birthday of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song and a series of measures for firm solidarity with the 
Korean people in their efforts to solve the nuclear issue of the 
Korean peninsula through the DPRK-USA negotiation. 

</TEXT>

