<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Marks Publication of Kim Il-song Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0903110394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1020 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0903110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Famous Work on Building Revolutionary Armed Forces of </F>
Chuche" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 9 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
carries an article on the lapse of 60 years since the great 
leader President Kim Il-song published the famous work "On 
Reorganizing the Anti-Japanese People's Guerrilla Army Into the 
Korean People's Revolutionary Army." 
  In the famous work on March 9, 1934, President Kim Il-song 
indicated a highly important guideline in the building of 
chuche-oriented revolutionary Armed Forces. Thus, he opened a 
new phase in the Army building and strengthened the combat 
capability of the revolutionary Armed Forces as required by the 
developing situation so as to expand the anti-Japanese armed 
struggle. 
  The author of the article says: 
  The great leader's work is a historic work which indicated 
the way of building chuche-oriented revolutionary Armed Forces 
on the basis of a scientific analysis of the lawful requirement 
of the military and political situation and the development of 
the guerrilla Army and the prospect of the revolutionary 
struggle to accomplish the cause of national liberation. 
  The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song taught: 
  "We must reorganize the anti-Japanese people's guerrilla 
Army 
into the Korean People's Revolutionary Army without delay as 
required by the prevailing military and political situation and 
the development of the anti-Japanese people's guerrilla Army." 
  In the work, the great leader said the Korean People's 
Revolutionary Army (KPRA) should be organised in the system of a 
regular Army and, at the same time, in such a system that it 
could strictly observe the principle of guerrilla warfare, 
taking it into consideration that the anti-Japanese armed 
struggle was being waged in the form of a guerrilla warfare 
against the regular Armed Forces of Japanese imperialism. He 
also formulated the organisational system of the KPRA. 
  He said the division, regiment, company, platoon and squad 
of 
the KPRA should be organised in a three-unit system, that the 
company should be defined as the main combat unit as required by 
the guerrilla warfare and that the KPRA units should be formed 
on the principle of strengthening the companies to the maximum. 
  In forming the units, unified command of the headquarters of 
the KPRA should be guaranteed and, to this end, the general 
staff should be strengthened and its role be enhanced as fully 
as possible, he said. 
  In the work, he put forward the policy of organizing the 
party committee of the KPRA in keeping with the reorganization 
of the anti-Japanese people's guerrilla Army into the KPRA. 
  As the great leader organized the party committee of the 
KPRA 
and enhanced its role, the KPRA party committee could smoothly 
give unified guidance to all the party committees and 
organisations within the KPRA and correctly guide the Korean 
revolution as a whole as the supreme leadership body. 
  With the great leader's unique idea of Army building fully 
embodied in forming the KPRA, the KPRA grew to be invincible 
revolutionary Armed Forces and played a decisive role in 
achieving victory in the anti-Japanese armed struggle. 
  The Korean People's Army [KPA], the heir to the glorious 
anti-Japanese armed struggle, defeated the U.S. imperialist 
aggressor forces that had boasted of being the "strongest" in 
the world. The KPA has grown stronger to be 
one-match-for-a-hundred revolutionary Army firmly prepared 
politically and ideologically and in military technique under 
the wise leadership of its supreme commander, respected General 
Kim Chong-il. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

