<H3> <TI>   Do Muoi Holds Talks With DPRK Party Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1003150994 Hanoi VNA in English 1430 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1003150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 10 -- General Secretary Do Muoi 
received in Ho Chi Minh City yesterday a delegation of the 
Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) led by Hwang Chang-yop, secretary 
of the party Central Committee in charge of external relations 
affairs, which paid an official friendship visit to Vietnam from 
March 7-10. 
  During the reception, General Secretary Do Muoi welcomed the 
visit as an important contribution to the consolidation and 
development of the friendship between the parties and peoples. 
He thanked the Korean people for their support for the 
Vietnamese people's struggle against US aggression. He 
reaffirmed that the Vietnamese party, Government and people have 
always supported the cause of socialist construction, and the 
struggle for peace, sovereignty and reunification of the Korean 
people. 
  For his part, Hwang Chang-yop informed Do Muoi of the 
achievements recorded by the Korean people in recent years, and 
expressed his wish to further develop the solidarity and 
friendship between the two parties and peoples. 
  Mr. Hwang conveyed president Kim Il-song's invitation to Mr. 
Do Muoi to visit the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. The 
Vietnamese leader accepted the invitation with pleasure. 
  DPRK Ambassador to Vietnam Han Min-chol was also present at 
the the event. 
  The same day, advisor to the party Central Committee Nguyen 
Van Linh received the Korean guests during which the former 
expressed his satisfaction at the fine development of the 
relationship between the two parties and peoples, and wished 
that it would be further developed. 
  Mr. Hwang also conveyed President Kim Il-song's invitation 
to 
Nguyen Van Linh to visit the DPRK and the latter accepted it 
with pleasure. 
  While in Vietnam, the WPK delegation met with Pham The 
Duyet, 
Politburo member of the Communist Party of Vietnam Central 
Committee [CPV CC] and secretary of the Hanoi party committee, 
Vo Tran Chi, Politburo member of the CPV CC and secretary of the 
Ho Chi Minh City party committee. It had working sessions with 
the Vietnam Union of Peace, Solidarity and Friendship 
Organizations, the Vietnam-DPRK Friendship Association and the 
Vietnam Committee for Solidarity With the Korean People. It 
also toured some economic and cultural establishments in Hanoi 
and Ho Chi Minh City. 
  The delegation left Ho Chi Minh City today, concluding its 
visit to Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

