<H3> <TI>   Vice President Visits Guinea Bissau 1-4 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903065694 Hanoi VNA in English 1427 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0903065694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 7 -- Vice President Nguyen Thi Binh 
paid an official visit to Guinea-Bissau from March 1-4, as guest 
of the Vice President of the State Council Mr. Vasco Cabral. 
  While in Guinea-Bissau, Vice President Nguyen Thi Binh paid 
a 
courtesy visit to President of the State Council Joao Bernando 
Vieira. She held talks with Vice President of the State Council 
Vasco Cabral. 
  During the talks, the two sides discussed orientations and 
measures to promote the cooperative relations in economic, trade 
and other fields between the two countries. They expressed 
their belief that the existing fraternal friendship and 
solidarity between vietnam and Guinea-Bissau is the `carved 
stone' for the two countries to enter into new cooperation 
conforming to the conditions and interests of each country. 
  At the end of the visit, the two sides issued a joint 
communique and signed agreement on economic, scientific and 
technological, cultural and trade cooperation. 
  On this occasion, Vietnamese businessmen who accompanied 
Vice 
President Nguyen Thi Binh signed minutes of understanding on 
good exchanges with their partners in Guinea Bissau. 
  Speaking to the press before leaving, Mrs Nguyen Thi Binh 
expressed her satisfaction at the good results of her visit to 
Guinea Bissau, the last leg of her Africa tour. She also 
expressed her belief that the traditional friendship between the 
two countries will further develop. 

