<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   International Conference on Cambodian Aid Held </TI></H3>
<H4>   Cambodian Premiers Arrive 9 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> OW0903005394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0013 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0903005394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 9 KYODO -- Cambodian co-Premiers Prince 
Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen arrived at Narita Airport 
Wednesday for a four-day stay in Japan to attend a conference on 
reconstruction aid for Cambodia. The premiers will also meet 
Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa during their first visit to 
Japan since their administration was launched in September. 
  They are accompanied by Prince Norodom Sirivut, deputy prime 
minister and foreign minister, Sam Rangsi, economy and finance 
minister, Chea Chanto, planning minister, and Keat Chhon, senior 
minister in charge of rehabilitation and development. 
  Delegations from 32 countries, the European Union and 12 
international organizations will attend the second meeting of 
the International Committee on Reconstruction of Cambodia 
(ICORC), scheduled for Thursday and Friday in Tokyo. 
  Participants will assess Cambodia's mid- to long-term aid 
requirements and discuss how to improve its capacity to absorb 
and utilize aid. 

</TEXT>

