<H3> <TI>   Rebel Opposes ASEAN Invitation for Burma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0803163694 Oslo Democratic Voice of Burma in Burmese 1430 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0803163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo Democratic Voice of Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dear Listeners: General Saw Bo Mya, chairman of 
the Democratic Alliance of Burma, DAB, in his letter to Thai 
Prime Minister Chaun Likphai noted that the State Law and Order 
Restoration Council [SLORC] military regime should not be 
invited to attend the forthcoming annual ASEAN ministerial 
meeting. 
  In the DAB declaration, dated 4 March, Gen. Saw Bo Mya cited 
SLORC's inability to implement basic human rights and democracy 
in Burma and looking at SLORC's present activities it clearly 
indicates their intention to cling on to power through the use 
of military force. At present, SLORC does not deserve to be 
invited to the annual ASEAN ministerial meeting. 
  The letter also noted ASEAN need to wait-and-see the 
improvements in SLORC's records before considering such an 
invitation. 
  It has been learned that Gen. Saw Bo Mya sent similar 
letters 
to other ASEAN members. The annual ASEAN ministerial meeting 
will be held in Bangkok, Thailand, in July. The Thai Government 
intends to invite the SLORC military regime as guest to the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

