<H3> <TI>   Companies Urged To Move to Danang EPZ </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903101994 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0903101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Malaysian labor-intensive companies have been urged 
to consider relocating their operations to the 
Malaysian-initiated export processing zone, or EPZ, to be set up 
in Danang, Vietnam. The sales launch of the EPZ in Danang with 
EPZ MASDA joint venture cooperation as developer, will be held 
on the 22d of this month. EPZ MASDA chairman, Datuk Michael Chen 
told a news conference in Kuala Lumpur that labor-intensive 
companies, especially those in the garment and shoe 
manufacturing businesses, should reconsider relocating to the 
EPZ. 
  EPZ MASDA is a joint venture between Malaysian South-South 
Corporation Limited and Quang Nam-Da Nang Export Processing Zone 
Development Corporation. The EPZ is the brainchild of both the 
prime ministers of Vietnam and Malaysia -- the result of Prime 
Minister Datuk Sri Dr Mahathir's visit to Hanoi in 1992. 

</TEXT>

