<H3> <TI>   Nouhak Phoumsavan Receives Cambodia's Chea Sim </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0803013594 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0803013594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 1200 on 5 March, His Excellency [H.E.] Nouhak 
Phoumsavan, president of the Lao People's Democratic Republic 
[LPDR], received a courtesy call from Samdech Chea Sim, chairman 
of the Kingdom of Cambodia National Assembly, at Hokham Hall in 
the capital of Vientiane on the occasion of the Cambodian's 
official friendship visit to the LPDR. 
  Their conversation took place in an atmosphere of intimacy 
and mutual understanding. H.E. Nouhak Phoumsavan hailed the 
high-level Kingdom of Cambodia National Assembly delegation and 
extended his warm welcome. H.E. Nouhak Phoumsavan and Samdech 
Chea Sim highly assessed the traditional relations of friendship 
between the Lao and Cambodian peoples. H.E. Nouhak Phoumsavan 
stressed that the intimate solidarity and affection between the 
Lao and Cambodian peoples represent fraternal, neighborly, and 
comradely ties nurtured by sharing weal and woe ever since 
ancient times. 
  On the same occasion, Samdech Chea Sim expressed his full 
appreciation for and satisfaction with the warm welcome accorded 
by H.E. Nouhak Phoumsavan. He highly valued the continuously 
increasing and developing relations of friendship, cooperation, 
and assistance between the two states and peoples. 

</TEXT>

