<H3> <TI>   Daily Supports Labor Rights `Struggle' in South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1003044694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0423 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1003044694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["No Repression Can Block Workers' Struggle, NODONG SINMUN" </F>
-- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- With no amount of 
repression can the Kim Yong-sam group block the South Korean 
workers' struggle for vital rights including wage hike, stresses 
NODONG SINMUN today. 
  The news analyst says: 
  Bus union members in six cities under the Federation of Auto 
Workers Unions of South Korea have courageously risen up in 
struggle in the current spring season of wage negotiation. 
Their demand for vital rights including wage hike is a devand 
for the payment for their work and a demand for the rights and 
conditions for a life worthy of human beings. It is the minimum 
demand they have raised on the last line of retreat. Refusing 
to meet this demand is tantamount to forcing the workers to die. 
  Nevertheless, the Kim Yong-sam fascist clique is threatening 
a "strong countermeasure," branding the workers' struggle for 
vital rights as "collective selfishness." 
  The harsher the fascist clique's suppression, the closer the 
ranks of the South Korean workers and the fiercer their fight 
for the vital rights and democracy. 

</TEXT>

