<H3> <TI>   VNS: ROK Soldiers Said To Admire Kim Chong-il </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0903104194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0903104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 9 (KCNA) -- Feelings of deep 
reverence for the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il are growing 
among South Korean puppet Army soldiers, the Seoul-based radio 
Voice of National Salvation (VNS) reported. 
  A Captain Kim of the 21st Division of the puppet Army, 
chatting with his pals over the situation recently, said the 
People's Army of the North under the command of General Kim 
Chong-il, the most famous general in the world, is an unrivalled 
strong Army. 
  He said: 
  "General Kim Chong-il, possessed of outstanding military 
strategy as his born gift, has built the People's Army into a 
well-disciplined, unrivalled strong Army. Unity between 
officers and men, Army-civilian unity, the arming of all the 
people and the fortification of the whole country are true looks 
of the mighty North." 
  Listening to him, a second lieutenant surnamed Choe said: 
  "The way of averting the danger of war, loving peace and 
achieving reunification, the ardent aspiration of the nation, is 
to hold in high esteem and uphold General Kim Chong-il, the most 
famous general in the world produced by our nation, as 
commander-in-chief of the national Army. Herein lies the way of 
warding off national disaster, the way for us to live, for the 
nation to live and the way of achieving reunification." 

</TEXT>

