<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports on Increase in Timber Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0903234694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1508 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0903234694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 9 (KCNA) -- Timber production is on 
an increase in Korea. 
  According to data available at the Ministry of Forestry, 
over 
23,000 more cubic metres of timber has been produced in the last 
one month than in the like period last year. 
  The Yanggang and Chagang provincial combined general bureau 
of forestry set themselves the a goal of carrying out the yearly 
timber production quotas at more than 75 percent in wintertime. 
Ty fulfilled the February production plans respectively at 107 
and 106.7 percent and are expanding the success this month. 
  The Sijung, Yonam and many other forestry stations are these 
days overfulfilling their daily production assignments by more 
than 30 percent through an effective control of machinery 
coupled with meticulous organisation of economic affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

