<H3> <TI>   Military Rebels Asked To Exercise Restraint </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903030394 Quezon City MALAYA in English 6 Mar 94 pp 1, 6 </F>
<F P=103> BK0903030394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City MALAYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Joy Gruta] </F>
  [Excerpt] Fort del Pilar, Baguio City -- Defense Secretary 
Renato de Villa urged Saturday military rebels to desist from 
making unnecessary propaganda which could create an atmosphere 
inimical to their ongoing peace talks with the government. 
  He made the statement in response to a call of the Young 
Officers Union (YOU) to the new graduates of the Philippine 
Military Academy (PMA) to pursue their goals of initiating 
reforms within the military establishment. 
  De Villa was the guest of honor at the parade and review and 
awarding ceremonies of PMA's Bantay Lakas [Watch Force] class. 
The graduation ceremonies will be held Sunday with President 
Ramos as guest. 
  The 224 graduating cadets include De Villa's son Patrick. 
  De Villa said he has brought to the attention of the 
government negotiating panel headed by Professor Alfredo Tadiar 
recent propaganda tactics of the Nationalist Revolutionary 
Alliance [as published] and YOU which he said sow confusion in 
the peace process. 
  He said he has also asked the government panel to ascertain 
if statements purportedly released by the group of former Lt. 
Col. Gregorio Honasan were genuine and authentic. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

