<H3> <TI>   Honda Plans To Open Showroom in Beijing in Apr </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0903080094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0720 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0903080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 9 KYODO -- Honda Motor Co. said 
Wednesday [9 March] it will open a showroom in Beijing on April 
6 to promote automobile sales in China. The showroom, the first 
such facility to be opened in Beijing by a Japanese automaker, 
will exhibit Legend and Accord models, Honda said. 
  At the same time, Honda's Hong Kong-based sales subsidiary, 
Honda Motor (China) Co., will launch active automobile-marketing 
efforts in China, company officials said. The wholly owned 
subsidiary was established in February 1993 to market and 
service Honda motorcycles, for which Chinese demand is 
increasing, the officials said. 
  Honda so far has sold automobiles in China through trading 
companies. The officials said Honda decided to have the 
subsidiary promote direct automobile marketing in China after 
Honda's auto exports to the country hit a record 12,200 vehicles 
last year. 

